<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="396" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">823.79625/3: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-03T19:00:00-05:00">August 3, 1929—7
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>147. Responsive to the message your telegram No. 79, July 31, 6 p.m.,
                                instructed me to convey, President Leguía authorized me to inform
                                President Hoover and yourself that he was entirely of your opinion
                                respecting the proposed conference. He will inform the Chilean
                                Government that because of Peru’s aviation commitments the Peruvian
                                Government is not free to participate in the proposed
                                conference.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>